Less than 24 hours since Kiernan &#8220;AKA&#8221; Forbes tweeted on Friday night that he and Bonang Matheba had called quits on their relationship, AKA tweeted on Saturday afternoon that he loved Bonang and they were &#8220;good&#8221;. READ MORE: AKA and Bonang have broken up Just before 2pm on Saturday, AKA tweeted the following, tagging Bonang: https://twitter.com/akaworldwide/status/832920769764216832 The tweet was retweeted 604 times and liked 747 times in just two hours. He followed the tweet with another, saying that &#8220;couples fight&#8221; and &#8220;life goes on&#8221;: https://twitter.com/akaworldwide/status/832920920427737093 AKA&#8217;s Friday night tweet announcing the break-up had read, &#8220;Sad to announce that myself and @bonang_m have broken up. We tried guys.&#8221; Bonang did not address the break-up on her Twitter account but on Saturday afternoon, she tweeted this photo: Saturday. pic.twitter.com/U7nUiRaJck &mdash; Bonang B* Matheba (@bonang_m) February 18, 2017 All of this will only add to the speculation that the &#8220;break-up&#8221; was just another publicity stunt. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.